page.title: 09NATURE AROUND PENCAITLAND
page.content: { }The Railway Walk starts at West Saltoun and carries on for about 6.5 miles to Crossgatehall.The wildlife along this walk is very interesting. There are some rabbits and hares,and the occasional stoat or weasel.The hawthorn trees are in full blossom.The little white cabbage butterflies fly around.There are different kinds of trees.Rowan trees,birch,bramble and hawthorn. There is a lot of plant life too.Dandelions,daisies,greater stitchwort.Bush vtech and water aven.Speedwell and forget-me-not.There are also nettles,thistles,moss and ferns. As well as this wildlife there are also some small garden birds.There are finches,wrens,tits,robins,thrushes and blackbirds.
